Unincorporated community in Florida, United States

Holopaw, Florida

An [unincorporated community](/Unincorporated_area) in [Florida](/Florida), if you truly must know, is a locale that exists without its own municipal government. It lacks the formal structures of a [city](/City) or town, meaning administrative services are typically provided by the surrounding [county](/List_of_counties_in_Florida). In this particular instance, we're discussing Holopaw, a rather unassuming stretch of existence within [Osceola County](/Osceola_County,_Florida), [Florida](/Florida), in the [United States](/United_States). It’s not a place that screams for attention, which, frankly, is often for the best.

